Defined by Codex Alimentarius standard CODEX STAN 280-1973, Anhydrous milkfat is a milk product containing almost no water and nonfat solids.  Anhydrous milk fat must contain at least 99.8 % milk fat and be made from fresh cream or butter. No additives are allowed, e.g. for neutralization of free fatty acids.
